Ad Text:
Most job ads for data engineers talk about “exciting opportunities” and “fast-paced environments.” Translation: you’ll be cleaning up spaghetti pipelines for the next two years.

This role isn’t that.

You’ll be the one setting the direction. The one deciding how data gets used, stored, and scaled. The one whose work powers AI models, analytics, and commercial decisions, not just another person duct-taping together broken queries.

Here’s what you’ll actually be doing:

Building pipelines in Azure that don’t collapse under their own weight.
Designing data architecture that can scale without burning money.
Creating infrastructure that makes machine learning models work in the real world.
Partnering with product and commercial teams so data isn’t just “available” but useful.
Putting proper governance and observability in place
What you need to bring:

Strong Azure knowledge: Data Factory, Synapse, Event Hubs, Functions, Storage.
Databricks, Elasticsearch, Python or .Net
A handle on data modelling, governance, and security that goes beyond theory.
Communication skills that don’t make commercial people back slowly out of the room.
Extra brownie points if you’ve:

Worked with Snowflake, Airflow, Kafka, MLflow, Feature Stores.
Built AI or propensity models that actually got used.
Seen the inside of a SaaS or startup and lived to tell the tale.
What’s in it for you:

Flexible hours and remote work – no surprises there.
The chance to build a data strategy from scratch, not inherit one from 2012.
A culture where you won’t be punished for learning.
Work that directly influences the success of the product
This isn’t a role for someone who wants to be told what to build. It’s for someone who wants to shape the whole data landscape.

nat@justdigitalpeople.com.au

Job Title: Director, Commercial Payments Practice Lead, Visa Consulting & Analytics
Ad Text:
Company Description


Visa is a world leader in payments and technology, with over 259 billion payments transactions flowing safely between consumers, merchants, financial institutions, and government entities in more than 200 countries and territories each year. Our mission is to connect the world through the most innovative, convenient, reliable, and secure payments network, enabling individuals, businesses, and economies to thrive while driven by a common purpose – to uplift everyone, everywhere by being the best way to pay and be paid.

Make an impact with a purpose-driven industry leader. Join us today and experience Life at Visa.

Job Description


Team Summary

Visa Consulting & Analytics (VCA) is Visa's consulting division, serving Visa's clients (including card issuers, acquirers, and merchants) and solving their strategic problems focused on improving performance and profitability.  Drawing on our expertise in strategy consulting, payments, data analytics, marketing, operational and macroeconomics, VCA drives high impact and tangible financial results.

The VCA team within Australia provides a comprehensive range of consulting services and solutions to our clients in Australia and New Zealand, that address unique challenges in areas such as strategic growth, profitability, risk management and digital strategy.        

The Role

We are currently looking for a Director to lead VCA’s Commercial Payments Practice for the AuNZPI region. The Commercial Payments Practice supports our clients to create and launch market-leading business payments solutions, derive greater value from the active management of their existing business cards portfolios, and identify new strategic growth opportunities. 

As the Practice lead, the Director will be responsible for growing the Commerical Payments Practice through business development, leading and delivering consulting engagements, and developing new solutions to continuously enhance and diversify the Practice’s client offerings.

In this role, the Director will lead a small team of consultants and collaborate with cross-functional experts across Visa’s business to jointly develop client proposals, participate in client sales activities and ensure client engagements are delivered with excellence. The full range of responsibilities are detailed below:

Responsibilities

On a project-by-project basis:

Prepare client project proposals, clarifying objectives, scope, deliverables, approach, dependencies, roles and responsibilities, draw input from clients, local client relationship managers and functional teams.
Oversee project setup including contracting documentation, stakeholder engagement, interview guides and client data requirements.
Develop a fact base by undertaking client interviews, collecting and analysing inputs such as client data, process flows, policies, competitive, industry and environmental information.
Analyse Visa and client data to conduct benchmarking, identify performance gaps and improvement opportunities.
Collaborate with data science team members to leverage data analytics capabilities
Manage execution of one or more project engagements, building client relationships, utilising governance frameworks and mitigating or resolving complex problems that emerge.
Identify solutions and recommendations that address client objectives and result in performance improvement, leverage relevant VCA methodologies, frameworks and global best practices.
Design and deliver compelling presentations to illustrate findings, ideas, recommendations within consulting engagements and more broadly and at times support implementation at the client onsite.

More generally:

Identify and surface opportunities for client projects.
Create, develop and maintain VCA IP and consulting offerings.
Continuously build knowledge, surface new insights and produce thought leadership pieces that contribute to practice development and global best practice.

This is a hybrid position. Expectation of days in office will be confirmed by your hiring manager. This role can be based in either Sydney or Melbourne.

Qualifications


Having already accumulated a variety of experience, you will be familiar with the payments industry and keen to work alongside an experienced team in gaining a deeper understanding. You will be client driven, comfortable managing a project end to end and relishing the opportunity to work closely with clients to influence their future performance.

Specific skills and experience you may bring are:

10+ years in consulting, business management or product management.
Deep experience in strategy consulting.
Deep experience in SMB or Corporate banking and / or payments solutions.
Deep experience in product P&L or portfolio management.
Superior analytical and problem solving skills, with demonstrated intellectual and analytical rigor.
Strong team orientation with a collaborative, diplomatic, and flexible style and be able to work effectively in a matrixed organisation.
Excellent detail orientation, ensuring the highest level of quality and rigour in reports and data analysis.
Excellent presentation skills, including strong oral and written capabilities.
Self-motivated, results-oriented individual with the ability to progress multiple priorities concurrently.
Experience in and passion for the power of analytics to inform and drive strategy and tactics, and proven ability to generate insights from data.
Strong commercial acumen, with experience in working on business cases that prove ROI.

Additional Information


Visa is an EEO Employer. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or protected veteran status. Visa will also consider for employment qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with EEOC guidelines and applicable local law.

Make a difference in your community:

Located in the south west suburbs of Melbourne, this organisation is committed to delivering essential services, improving liveability, and shaping the future for residents and businesses. In this role, you’ll contribute to a meaningful project that supports better outcomes for the community.

About the role:

As a Data Analyst, you'll be responsible for analysing data from system-based records (specifically Greenlight) to identify trends, support adherence to service delivery expectations and improve compliance processes.  

The role involves managing compliance data, creating dashboards, developing and tracking Key Performance Indicators (KPIs), providing insights for decision-making, and contributing to the implementation of compliance strategies, policies and procedures to enhance service delivery.

Key responsibilities include:

Data Collection & Analysis:  Inspecting, cleansing, and transforming building-related data to extract valuable information.
Compliance Monitoring:  Tracking adherence to standards and performance requirements.
Risk Assessment:  Identifying risks related to non-compliance and contributing to risk-based compliance strategies.
Reporting & Visualisation:  Building dashboards, trackers, and reports to communicate compliance status and insights to stakeholders.
Process Improvement:  Contributing to new approaches and strategies for regulatory practices and enforcement.
About you:

Proven experience in a data analyst or business intelligence role.
Advanced Excel skills, including pivot tables, formulas, and data modelling.
Proficiency in data visualisation and BI tools.
Knowledge of statistical analysis techniques.
Ability to analyse large datasets, identify trends, and draw meaningful conclusions.
Experience with Greenlight will be highly advantageous.

To apply or for more information, please reach out to Rick Kelly - Rick@publicsectorpeople.com.au

Do work that matters

The Group Treasury team at CBA supports the business and customers by providing a strong and resilient balance sheet. The team works closely with stakeholders across the Group, to provide expertise and insights on balance sheet management.


See yourself in our Team

We are looking for Senior Managers to join the Balance Sheet, Efficiency & Resilience Team, with roles in the Group Stress Testing and Liquidity Stress Testing teams. In these roles, you will manage a team of analysts to apply advanced analytics to project the Group's balance sheet and financial performance across a range of scenarios. Your work will provide critical insights and assurance on the Group's resilience during periods of uncertainty.

As a Senior Manager, you will:


Lead the development and execution of financial and risk models to assess profitability, capital, credit, and liquidity impacts under various stress scenarios.
Prepare high-quality presentations and reports to communicate key insights and model outcomes to senior leadership.
Work with and maintain strong collaborative relationships with stakeholders across the Group, including Finance and Risk Management.
Manage and mentor a team of Analysts and Senior Analysts, fostering a high-performance culture.
Support Group Treasury in managing the Group's balance sheet, including capital, liquidity, and funding strategies.
Contribute to regulatory stress testing exercises and ensure compliance with relevant requirements.
Drive continuous improvement in stress testing methodologies, processes, and tools.


We're interested in hearing from people who have


Tertiary qualifications in mathematics, statistics, engineering, economics or similar quantitative discipline.
Proficiency in data management and programming skills such as SQL, R, Python and SAS.
Experience credit risk modelling (Internal Ratings Based or IFRS9) and/or financial modelling is highly desirable.
Understanding of the Australian prudential regulatory environment, including relevant APS prudential standards.
Strong organisational, planning, and project management skills, with a proven ability to deliver high-quality outcomes under pressure and within tight timeframes.
Ability to interact with a large and varied stakeholder group. Ability to develop and manage sustained relationships with internal and external stakeholders.
Risk Mindset - All CommBank employees are expected to proactively identify and understand, openly discuss and act on current and future risks.


We support our people with the flexibility to balance where work is done with at least half your time each month connecting in our office. We also have many other flexible working options available including changing start and finish times, part-time arrangements and job share to name a few. Talk to us about how these arrangements might work for you.




Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career here is for you.

Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive and flexible workplace. We are working hard to build a team of people who represent the rich diversity of our customers and communities. If you're excited about this opportunity but you don't meet every single requirement, or your experience doesn't align perfectly, we still want to encourage you to apply. You may just be the perfect candidate for this opportunity or another within CommBank.

At CommBank we will inspire you with work that makes a difference, surround you with talented people that respect and value each other, and empower you to grow professionally and personally. Most of all, making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.

We're determined to make a real difference for Australia's first peoples. We encourage all interested applicants to apply. If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest), you'll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We're keen to support you with the next step in your career.

We've been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with 120,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you'll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you'll also get to see your impact.

About the team

As the way we shop continues to evolve, our Data and Artificial Intelligence Team keeps us at the cutting edge. Driven by our innovative, inclusive, and forward-thinking culture, we’re constantly looking at ways to reinvent the shopping experience for our customers and build the next generation of digital retailing. 

The Data and Artificial Intelligence within the broader Coles Technology Team focuses on building data collection and analytics capabilities to uncover customer, product, and operational insights. Providing data driven support to our users and enabling Coles to be a data driven organisation.

About the role

For this exciting position within our Data and Artificial Intelligence team, we are seeking a versatile Product Manager to manages the end-to-end delivery of specific AI and data products, ensuring business value is realised.

Also, be responsible for creating the roadmap for product squad of multi-disciplinary engineers. Accountable for the results of squads using agile product delivery methods to deliver data and AI products that deliver measurable value to the business.

Working closely with the Group Product Manager Data & AI, your main responsibilities will include the following but not be limited to the below:

Defines backlog with their squads, partners with the domain stakeholders to ensure the backlog aligns with the business and product strategies. Frame the product backlog with bigger picture thinking that is anchored to the domain’s strategic priorities and long-term vision. Utilises strategy and product roadmap to define quarterly objectives and key success measures for squads.
Manages and prioritises backlog to deliver on their quarterly objectives and key commercial outcomes. Responsible for end-to-end execution of their initiatives, from discovery to delivery
Ability to lead Data & AI component of complex cross-functional initiatives and projects. Fosters and maintains strong stakeholder relationships to ensure transparency and alignment around backlog, priorities and key deliverables.
Works closely with Engineering Manager, development squad and vendor partners to manage delivery, dependencies and risk.
Communicates to domain stakeholders on progress of initiatives. Foster close engagement with business stakeholders, promoting Data and AI literacy and influencing stakeholders on how data and AI can drive their strategy and business outcomes.
Partner with stakeholders across business and technology to influence strategic priorities and investment decisions.

Product Leadership

Define the product vision, strategy and roadmap for assigned Data and AI products.
Gather, manage and prioritise product requirements as inputs to squads. Translate business needs into clearly defined epics, user stories, and acceptance criteria.
Manage delivery through discovery, design, build, testing, deployment, and adoption phases. Continue to monitor products in use for further enhancements, support or remediation.
Ensure a high standard of product practices across the portfolio, including hypothesis validation/proof of concept, roadmap development, feature prioritisation, release planning, and benefits realisation.

Stakeholder Engagement

Act as a strategic partner to business and technology stakeholders, influencing priorities, communicating vision, and aligning roadmaps for Data and AI Products. Be able to participate in strategy development sessions with influence.
Ensure alignment between product features and business value drivers.
Guide the business to make Buy, Build and Partner decisions for AI solutions.
Communicate product delivery updates and translate complex technical or delivery information into clear business context to support prioritisation and decision-making.

Product Operations and Governance

Take ownership of Data and AI products including defining value metrics and monitoring product success.
Lead in-house multidisciplinary squads to deliver value incrementally, applying agile product management principles such as iterative delivery, continuous feedback loops, and backlog prioritisation (balancing new development, enhancement, stability, tech debt remediation and support needs).
Define the release objectives and coordinate the wider go live activities associated with a release in conjunction with iteration manager.

Experience required

Proven experience as a Product Manager or equivalent in large scale enterprise setting, with specific experience in developing AI products
Strong domain experience in data science, machine learning concepts and generative AI models. Agentic AI systems experience preferred. 
Familiarity with MLOps, LLMOps and continuous model monitoring frameworks. Familiarity with data platform technologies (e.g. Databricks, Snowflake). 
Understanding of retail data sources as relevant to domain (POS, loyalty, commercial, inventory, supply chain, workforce) and how they can be applied to AI use cases.
Track record of leading multi-disciplinary squads in an agile product delivery environment.
Experience using customer insight, data, and commercial outcomes to shape product decisions and prioritisation.
Involved in defining product success metrics and monitoring product success
Strong ability to deliver and execute on agreed delivery plans, prioritise development requirements and manage output to critical milestones 
Proven track record of building strong relationships with multiple business stakeholders and teams, with an ability to bridge technical and business perspectives and influence leaders in domain.

Commercial Skills and Formal Qualifications

Mid-level experience in product management or equivalent role with data and AI related products
Ability to develop and articulate a long-term vision for one or more proposed technology solutions, balancing a solution and project view with a systems and enterprise view.
Ability to contextualise a program of work within a broader context, such as analysing second order implications of a possible solution. Ability to identify marketplace opportunities and discover the most appropriate ways and time to capitalise on them.
Awareness of the competitive landscape of emerging business models reshaping the retail industry, with demonstrated expertise in emerging AI technology, including Agentic and Generative AI, providing the ability to identify opportunities, challenges, and competitive threats from these emerging technologies and how they might impact retail.
Understanding of with the full Technology Lifecycle, including both software and AI/data science development cycles, with key stages and responsibilities, technologies, vendors, and roles.
Tertiary qualifications in Business, Technology, Design, or related fields (or equivalent work experience).
Excellent strategic thinking and commercial acumen, with the ability to connect product delivery to business impact.
Outstanding communication and storytelling skills, with the ability to inspire and align diverse stakeholders.
Strong capability in product planning tools and frameworks (e.g. OKRs, JTBD, value stream mapping, roadmapping).

What’s in it for you? 

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.

Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.

Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hot deals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.

Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks.’ You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.

Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.

Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.

Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

About the recruitment process

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

Employment Type: Full time 

#LI-MM1

Our client is responsible for the adjudication of camera detected offence images and issuing and processing of infringement notices. This Government Department collects and enforces unpaid fines and court orders. They are also responsible for collecting state taxes (including duties, payroll tax and land tax) and mining and petroleum royalties and administering certain grants.
the Department takes a client centric approach to help their clients meet their obligations and receive their correct entitlements. 
 
Background
Seeking an experienced IT Project Manager to lead three strategic initiatives: 

Data Maturity Uplift Project – improving organisational data governance, quality, and analytics maturity.
Business Process Documentation & Gap Analysis Project – documenting core business processes, identifying gaps, and defining requirements for improvement.
Project coordination for the InfoSec program of works
 
This role will oversee planning, execution, stakeholder engagement, and delivery across all 3 streams, ensuring outcomes align with organisational strategy and Enterprise Architecture governance frameworks.
 
Key responsibilities of the Role:
 
Project Management & Delivery

Develop detailed project management plans, change management plans, communications plans, quality plans, detailed project schedules, and resource schedules, inclusive of budget for above mentioned initiatives.
Ensure delivery within agreed scope, timeframes, and quality standards.
Establish governance and reporting mechanisms, including steering committees and executive updates.
Schedule, review, monitor and evaluate project progress and report on such to key stakeholders including project governance bodies, and the program manager.
Ensure project risks and issues are promptly identified and effectively managed and that project stakeholders are informed and engaged in project development and implementation activities.
 
Stakeholder & Team Leadership

Provide leadership and management of projects, within established project management frameworks, methodologies, and policies, to ensure successful project outcomes.
Engage with executives, business SMEs, and technical teams to ensure alignment and buy-in.
Facilitate workshops for data governance and process documentation activities.
Manage vendors, consultants, and internal delivery resources.
Facilitate team and individual development and build positive and participative culture aligned to our values and expectations.
Provide effective leadership to the project team comprised of Data Engineers, Data Analysts, Reports developers, Enterprise Architects, Business users and take appropriate action where team performance deviates from agreed tolerances.
 
Data Maturity Uplift

Coordinate maturity assessments, uplift activities, and improvement initiatives.
Support adoption of data governance, metadata management, data quality, and reporting practices.
Track and report on KPIs such as data quality metrics and maturity benchmarks.
Ensure regulatory and policy compliance and strong data governance.
Ensure data lakehouse strategically aligns with the business goals and organisational objectives.
 
Business Process Documentation & Gap Analysis

Lead process-mapping workshops with business units.
Document As-Is processes in standard notation (e.g., BPMN). o Identify gaps, risks, and inefficiencies; define To-Be processes and requirements.
Deliver consolidated process maps, gap analysis, and requirements registers.
 
Change & Communication

Develop communication plans and support change management activities.
Ensure knowledge transfer to business and IT stakeholders.
 Required to train up and handover to existing staff and document to an acceptable standard
 

Required Skills & Experience

5–10 years’ experience managing IT/business transformation projects.
Strong project management expertise (PRINCE2, PMBOK, or Agile/Hybrid delivery).
Demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously.
Excellent stakeholder engagement, facilitation, and communication skills.
Proven experience in delivering projects involving data governance, data quality, or analytics initiatives.
Experience in business process documentation, analysis, and requirements gathering.
Strong risk, issue, and dependency management.
 
Desirable Skills & Qualifications

Relevant certifications: PMP, PRINCE2 Practitioner, Agile (Scrum Master), or TOGAF.
Knowledge of data maturity models (e.g., DAMA-DMBOK, DCAM, CMMI).
Experience in the public sector or highly regulated industries.
Exposure to enterprise architecture, data platforms, or business transformation programs.
BPM certification (e.g., ABPMP, OCEB) highly regarded. Attributes
Strong analytical and problem-solving mindset.
High emotional intelligence with the ability to influence and manage resistance.
Comfortable working in complex, ambiguous environments.
Adaptable, pragmatic, and delivery-focused.

Financial Performance & Analysis Lead - APAC




About the Business and Team

At SLR, our purpose is to Make Sustainability Happen. SLR is an international environmental consultancy with a globally recognised reputation for providing high quality, tailored services. With over 1,000 staff in the APAC region, we provide expert advice and support on a wide range of sustainability challenges to a growing client base of businesses, regulatory and governmental organisations. We are proud to be one of the few leading international specialist environmental consultancies.

Our Finance team has an opportunity for a Financial Performance & Analysis Lead to head initiatives in the APAC region. This role has the preference to be based out of our Sydney, Brisbane, Melbourne, Newcastle or Wollongong office.

As part of our growing Finance team, the role plays a key role in driving financial performance across the APAC region. This commercially focused role partners with Project Leaders, Service Line Managers, and the Regional Management Team to improve project returns, support better decision-making, and enhance financial accountability.

You’ll lead budgeting, forecasting, reporting, and analysis across teams, providing visibility into key trends, risks, and opportunities. As a strategic partner to the APAC Finance Director, you’ll deliver insights that shape decisions, drive operational efficiency, and support sustainable growth.







Job Tasks and Responsibilities

Collaborate with service line and project leaders and the APAC Finance Director to support and offer valuable financial insight to improve performance improvement, strategic decision making around bids, hiring and initiatives.

Lead the development and continuous improvement of financial forecasts and performance reports at team and portfolio levels

Working with the Global FP&A team to coordinate the APAC annual budgeting process and variance analysis ensuring alignment across regions, service lines, and support functions. Including the preparation of a three-statement budget (P&L, Balance Sheet and Cash Flow).

Provide financial, commercial and scenario analyses and financial models to support business planning, investment decisions and delivery planning.

Monitor margin and multiplier performance, working with delivery teams to improve profitability and reduce write-offs.

Help implement and maintain controls for WIP, AR, revenue recognition and project provisioning.

Support the refinement of standard commercial reporting and controls to improve consistency and accountability.

Work with Business Improvement and Finance to strengthen commercial capability among Project Managers and Project Support Officers.

Help simplify tools and templates that support project financial performance and empower teams to self-manage effectively.







Skills and Experience

Degree in accounting or finance with CA/CPA or MBA required

5–10 years’ experience in Financial Planning & Analysis, commercial finance, or project performance roles.

Strong understanding of project-based financials including revenue recognition, margin, WIP and utilisation.

Proven ability to manage forecasts, budgets, and performance reporting across large or complex portfolios

Experience partnering with non-financial stakeholders to influence business outcomes.

Strong analytical skills with high proficiency in Excel; Power BI or similar tools desirable.

Excellent written and verbal communication skills – able to translate financial information into clear operational advice.

Comfortable working at pace and balancing competing priorities across teams.

Experience in consulting, engineering, or other professional services organisations is highly desirable.







Our Benefits

SLR offers a collaborative and flexible workplace, with a clear commitment to sustainability and professional growth. You’ll join a team that values insight, action, and accountability, and can shape how finance supports a high-performing, purpose-led business.

We are most proud of our expert teams and unique culture where we work together to collaborate on projects to get the best possible outcome for our clients and our team. Our benefits aim to ensure that we cater for all.

Melbourne is Australia's fastest growing city - a city that is becoming increasingly reliant on public transport networks. Since 2009, Metro proudly continues to operate and maintain a world-class train service and network through to delivering significant transport projects that will shape how Melbourne moves. With Zero Harm at the foundation of everything we do, we want everyone to get home safely. We are one team, helping to connect and shape a better Melbourne.





The Business and Commercial Analyst is responsible for providing in-depth commercial analysis through reviewing commercial contracts for the development of contractual claims and variations and leading the end-to-end process of claims, from investigation, financial modelling, to the approval by the Department of Transport.

Reporting to the OCMS Contractual Claims Manager, this role will collaborate across internal teams to collect the necessary information and develop complex financial models to present and submit variations claims to the Department of Transport to reach commercial outcomes.

This is a 2 year opportunity located at 700 Collins Street at our headoffice in Docklands.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

Commercial and financial analysis to support OCMS strategic priorities.
Quality checks and validating claim Net Financial Impacts including the identification of cost areas.
Development of variation claims, through investigation of financial analysis, contracts, and other data sources, ensuring timely and accurate resolution of financial matters
Engage key stakeholders across the team, division, and broader organisation to collate the required information for claims.
Validation and collation of actual costs for preparation of claims.
Manage delivery pipeline to progress against plan and ensure timely delivery and take effective remedial action as required.
Financial modelling experience.
Preparing reporting for forecasts and actuals of claims completed.
Submission of the annual forecast to the Department of Transport and Planning (DTP)

ABOUT YOU

Tertiary qualification in Financial or Business Management.
Ability to analyse data and write and present reports, undertake and complete complex tasks.
Experience with commercial contracts.
Ability to understand and review commercial contracts for financial and forecasting.
Experience and knowledge of key accounting concepts.
Experience with the preparation and collation of financial information.
Development of complex financial models or operational performance reporting.
Knowledge of technology assets, asset lifecycle preferred.
Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Excel.
Experience with data modelling and dashboard creation.
Ability to automate tasks using VBA or macros.
Experience with Power Query and Power BI integration.

NEXT STEPS

If this role resonates with your values, experience, and career needs, then come join us and help connect people and places for a growing Melbourne!

Don't meet every single requirement? As an inclusive and diverse workplace, we encourage all applicants to apply. Applications close on Sunday 12th October 2025.

Metro is committed to making reasonable adjustments to provide a positive, barrier-free recruitment process for candidates with specific access needs. Candidates who require adjustments are encouraged to declare this in their application, so that the contact person for the position can discuss your needs.





WHY WORK AT METRO?

Work for a multi-award-winning rail operator with rewarding career opportunities that provide you with the support and training to take your career to the next level!
Be part of an inclusive, diverse, and supportive company made up of various backgrounds, cultures, and experiences.
Work-life balance options including flexible working arrangements, 14 weeks paid parental leave, and purchasing up to 4 weeks of additional leave per year.
All eligible Metro employees receive a free Myki Pass that allows free Public Transport in Victoria.
Access to a wide range of corporate discounts including healthcare, fitness, finance, and more.

An experienced Change Manager / Business Analyst is needed for a key role in a transformation project with one of Queensland’s iconic organisations. This role will be central to redesigning processes, supporting system improvements and driving meaningful change across a complex, multi-site environment.
  
About the Role
Reporting into a Senior Project Manager, you will step into a pivotal role within a significant transformation program with both an ERP and process change focus.
This encompassing project has been underway for some time and has shifted to now focusing on major supply chain projects, including advanced warehouse management and material requirements planning across multiple sites, including over 200 warehouses.
  
This position will see you:

Lead process design and change activities across sourcing, purchasing, and payments
Partner closely with a range of senior stakeholders to align priorities and secure buy-in across the organisation
Map processes, redesign operating models, and influence system design (Dynamics365) to support improved supply chain practices
Provide guidance to a team of analysts and change professionals already engaged in delivery
Drive engagement, communication, and training to ensure lasting change across a complex environment
About You
We’re looking for a senior operator with proven experience in large-scale transformation. Ultimately, there is a level of pragmatism and flexibility about the exact skillset you bring, so if you have some of the below, but not all, I would encourage you to apply.
  
 You will bring:

A track record leading change in ERP implementations or remediation (D365 advantageous)
Experience working in large, complex organisations
Strong knowledge of supply chain and P2P processes – MRP or AWM transformation highly regarded
Exceptional stakeholder management skills with the ability to influence at executive level
A collaborative style and the ability to cut through complexity to deliver results
  
Why Join?

An initial 12-month contract with potential for extensions or permanency
Attractive package of $180k + superannuation + NFP salary sacrifice
A flexible, delivery-focused culture. Inner suburbs based, with significant WFH and flexibility on offer
Opportunity to contribute to a once-in-a-career transformation project in a major healthcare organisation
How to Apply:
Please apply to this advertisement directly. If you have specific questions or want to share any additional information, please feel free to reach out at lucas@c3talent.com.au

Job Title: Principal Business Analyst - Duck Creek Policy
Ad Text:
Join a large Business Analyst community where ideas and best practice are shared.
Must have technical Duck Creek Policy Administration System (PAS) experience. (min 5 years)
Hybrid Working model, supportive and collaborative culture.

 

We’re never just satisfied with how things are – because we know how things could be. And it’s our expert Technology team who forge ahead every day to make those ‘what ifs’ a reality.

Welcome to a place where you can chase real progress and drive real change. And that includes your own career. Being a part of Technology at Suncorp Group means being switched on, endlessly curious and always adaptable. In return, you’ll be supported to bring your own ideas to the table and challenge conventions – with the aim of making life a little brighter, simpler, and better for our customers and each other.

 

Overview of the role

We are looking for a Principal Business Analyst with proven Duck Creek PAS experience for a key role in the Duck Creek Policy Platform Core technology team which provides assurance, governance, specialist consultancy, functional leadership and solutions to project delivery and support teams.

Be part of Suncorp’s once in a generation policy transformation program (Digital Insurer) and help us aspire to be the Insurer of choice across the Trans-Tasman.   Leveraging market leading technology, including Duck Creek on Demand, work, learn & collaborate with the best – we are using SMEs and consultants from across the globe to build this market leading platform.

The program will enable the business to deliver new products (including modular products), more seamless customer experiences, and support the delivery of a simpler, digital business.  Radical simplification and significant improvement in the speed & cost of change are a critical measure of success of the program and it’s essential this role influences and champions this across the entire program and more broadly across the enterprise.

You will also be part of our large Analysis Chapter that consists of around 280 like-minded analysts, where ideas and best practice are shared via masterclasses and knowledge sharing.

Suncorp is proud of our fantastic culture where you will be supported in your career development.

 What you’ll do:

As the Duck Creek Principal BA, work closely with others in the DC Policy Platform core team and the Business design core team to provide functional leadership, governance, assurance, specialist consultancy and solutions to project delivery and support teams.
Build strong relationships through engagement with colleagues, and stakeholders across Business and Technology.
Document current and future state processes and identify opportunities for improvement.
Use information gathering techniques to proactively discover requirements and synthesise information accurately, completely, and coherently.
Work collaboratively with delivery teams, business and technology stakeholders to gather, validate and document business requirements and develop recommendations and solutions that meet business and customer needs. Raise, and support mitigation and resolution of, risks and issues using established tools and frameworks were applicable.
Create detailed user stories (in JIRA) to support delivery.
Document Technical design, Functional and Non-Function Requirements, PL101 completion, Policy Data Model updates, Interface/Integration mapping, Migration Mapping, Technical support documentation & Knowledge Bases
Work close with squad / project members, including but not limited to Project Manager, Scrum Master, Architects, Developers, Tech Leads, Test Analyst to identify, capture, plan and deliver changes
Mentor/train team members; participate and contribute to Business Analyst chapter and/or forums providing insights and thought leadership
Suncorp offers a hybrid way of working where you will be expected to be in the office approx. 2 days per week.

  What you’ll bring:

Minimum of 5 years’ experience with Duck Creek Policy Administration systems.
Strong understanding of Duck Creek standards, inheritance model, ideally experience with Duck Creek on Demand (DCOD), and experience with documenting requirements with development accelerators including PL101 and Technical Solution Blueprints.
Training and certification in Duck Creek university and related certification desired.
Minimum 8 years business analysis experience in General Insurance project/delivery roles, including the desired level of technical knowledge and expertise in Duck Creek
Ideally be Certified Business Analysis Professional (CBAP)
Must be able to translate and understand business and technical requirements and provide appropriate alternatives and solutions to meet those requirements.
Strong stakeholder engagement, relationship management and influencing skills including experience in dealing with various stakeholders.
Strong problem-solving and negotiation skills
Strong team player with a positive attitude, willingness to learn and mentor, and desire to make a difference.
Must be able to manage multiple complex initiatives with competing deadlines.

What we can offer you:

Discounts and offers on a range of retail favourite stores as well as insurance products.
A range of flexible working and leave options, including 20 weeks paid parental leave, 4 weeks paid secondary carer parental leave and unlimited paid emergency response leave.
Invest in your brighter future with ongoing study support and career development programs.
Give back to our communities with payroll giving, donation matching and paid volunteer leave.
Prioritise your work/life balance with our robust employee assistance program and dedicated employee council.

 

About Suncorp:

For over 100 years Suncorp has been driven by our guiding Purpose – to build futures and protect what matters. To ensure we deliver on that Purpose, we’ve made a commitment, built on trust, empowerment, and flexibility – to help our people unlock their full potential and unleash their best and brightest selves. With the backing and support of some of the most trusted names in insurance, the Suncorp family provides our people with every opportunity to grow their career as they make a meaningful difference for our customers and our communities. We’re excited about what we can achieve together, working every day to be better, do more and realise the future we want to see just beyond the horizon.

If this opportunity sounds like the challenge you have been looking for, please apply online today. 

Employee benefits | Suncorp Group

At Suncorp we believe we are our best when our workforce is as diverse, talented and passionate as the communities in which we live and operate, and where our people feel included, valued and connected. We are passionate about inspiring our people by creating a diverse, accessible, and inclusive culture, offering flexible work, career development and internal mobility, and building connected relationships amongst our team members and with our customers.

If you require any support and adjustments to participate equitably in our recruitment process or in the workplace, we encourage you to contact melissa.turkington@suncorp.com.au for a confidential conversation.

Data Analytics Manager
Full-Time | 2 Year Fixed Term | Sydney | $165,000 + 12% Super

About the Role

We are seeking an experienced Data Analytics Manager to lead a high-performing team and drive the delivery of advanced data and analytics capabilities across the arts and cultural sector.

This is an exciting opportunity to shape the organisation’s data strategy, optimise data pipelines and deliver insights that inform decision-making at the highest levels. You will oversee enterprise analytics architecture, mentor a skilled team and ensure best practice in data governance, engineering and analytics delivery.

Key Responsibilities

Lead and manage a data and analytics team, fostering continuous improvement and delivery excellence.
Oversee the development, optimisation and refinement of enterprise data models, pipelines, and metadata management.
Drive adoption of cloud-native solutions, leveraging Azure Synapse Analytics, Databricks and Azure DevOps.
Deliver advanced analytics and machine learning solutions that support strategic outcomes.
Ensure compliance with governance, security and regulatory standards.
Provide actionable insights and high-quality reporting to senior executives and stakeholders.
Monitor emerging trends in data engineering, analytics, AI/ML and advise on opportunities for adoption.
 
About You

To succeed in this role you will bring:

Proven experience in data engineering, information management or analytics leadership.
Strong track record leading teams delivering cloud-native data solutions.
Technical expertise in Azure Synapse Analytics, Databricks and Azure DevOps.
Experience with enterprise data modelling, data warehousing and analytics architecture.
Ability to translate technical concepts into business value for non-technical stakeholders.
Strong influencing and stakeholder management skills.
Excellent communication and problem-solving abilities.

Desirable:

Tertiary qualifications in a relevant field.
Experience delivering AI initiatives in business or the public sector.
Consulting or advisory experience.
 
What’s on Offer

In addition to a competitive salary of $165,000 + 12% superannuation, you will enjoy:

Hybrid work model - 2 days from home and 3 days on site in Sydney.
Flexible working hours to balance personal and professional life.
Additional paid leave between Christmas and New Year.
Paid cultural leave to observe personal religious or cultural obligations.
Access to wellbeing programs, corporate discounts and a holistic Employee Assistance Program for you, your family and kin.

How to Apply

If you are a data leader passionate about driving impact through analytics and information management and want to make a real difference in the arts and cultural sector, we encourage you to apply. Reach out to Lee Bartlett for more information - lee@bluefinresources.com.au

Based at Knoxfield (moving to Mulgrave in May, 2026)
Full time permanent position
Great team and work environment

Purpose

To operationalise data governance across the organisation’s analytics environment—ensuring data is accurate, secure, well-defined, and responsibly managed. The role translates policy into practice across tools like Informatica, Azure Data Factory, Databricks, dbt, and BI platforms.

Key Responsibilities

Framework Enablement: Translate policies into practical tools and coordinate governance forums
Metadata & Cataloguing: Curate glossaries, drive lineage/classifications, maintain tagging conventions
Data Quality Management: Define and automate DQ rules, monitor SLAs, triage issues
Integration & Transformation Controls: Apply governance in Informatica, ADF, Databricks, dbt
Risk, Privacy & Compliance: Conduct PIAs, ensure APPs compliance
Change & Training: Create playbooks, run enablement sessions
Reporting: Maintain governance scorecards and domain health reports

Key Competencies, Skills and Qualifications

Tertiary degree in Information Systems, Data/Computer Science or equivalent
Desirable certifications: Azure, Databricks, dbt, Informatica, Collibra, IAPP
3–6 years in data governance/data quality
Hands-on with at least two of: Informatica, Azure Data Factory, Databricks, dbt
Strong SQL and data modelling knowledge
Experience with data catalogs (Purview, Collibra, Alation) and lineage tools
Proven DQ automation and privacy/security understanding
Excellent stakeholder engagement skills

What PFD is Offering the Successful Candidate

We are offering competitive remuneration, superannuation and other staff benefits (such as discounts on staff purchases, discounted accommodation, health insurance and banking).

Melbourne is Australia's fastest growing city - a city that is becoming increasingly reliant on public transport networks. Since 2009, Metro proudly continues to operate and maintain a world-class train service and network through to delivering significant transport projects that will shape how Melbourne moves. With Zero Harm at the foundation of everything we do, we want everyone to get home safely. We are one team, helping to connect and shape a better Melbourne.





The Business Analyst is responsible for the development of contractual claims and variations, in line with the OCMS franchise module contractual obligations. You will be involved in the end-to-end process of claims, including data collection across multiple functions and assets and financial modelling, to the submission to the Department of Transport.

Reporting to the OCMS Contractual Claims Manager the Business Analyst will collaborate across internal teams to collect the necessary information and develop and utilise financial models to present and submit variations claims to the Department of Transport to reach commercial outcomes.

This is a 2 year opportunity located in Docklands at our Head Office

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

Complete analysis and documentation to support OCMS strategic priorities
Engage key stakeholders across the team, division, and broader organisation to collate the required information for claims.
Support the development of variation claims, including contractual and financial analysis and validation of technical asset details
Complete financial modelling to prepare contractual claims and variations for submission.
Collect and manipulate data from various sources to compile into the necessary frameworks required for submission to the Department of Transport and Planning (DTP)
Engage with Project Management and Engineering teams to collect the artefacts required for the retention submission
Liaise with internal finance teams and DTP to ensure the accuracy and the timely completion of the retention submission
Maintaining and updating forecasts and actuals as claims are completed.

ABOUT YOU

Tertiary qualification in Business or Financial Management
Ability to analyse data and write and present reports, undertake and complete complex tasks
Ability to communicate to staff at all levels (verbal & written)
Familiarity and knowledge of key accounting concepts.
Experience with the preparation and collation of financial information and project management methodologies is desirable.
Financial modelling experience
Knowledge of technology assets, asset lifecycle preferred.
Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Excel.
Familiarity with VBA, macros, Power Query and Power BI integration.

NEXT STEPS

If this role resonates with your values, experience, and career needs, then come join us and help connect people and places for a growing Melbourne!

Don't meet every single requirement? As an inclusive and diverse workplace, we encourage all applicants to apply. Applications close Sunday 12th October 2025.

Metro is committed to making reasonable adjustments to provide a positive, barrier-free recruitment process for candidates with specific access needs. Candidates who require adjustments are encouraged to declare this in their application, so that the contact person for the position can discuss your needs.





WHY WORK AT METRO?

Work for a multi-award-winning rail operator with rewarding career opportunities that provide you with the support and training to take your career to the next level!
Be part of an inclusive, diverse, and supportive company made up of various backgrounds, cultures, and experiences.
Work-life balance options including flexible working arrangements, 14 weeks paid parental leave, and purchasing up to 4 weeks of additional leave per year.
All eligible Metro employees receive a free Myki Pass that allows free Public Transport in Victoria.
Access to a wide range of corporate discounts including healthcare, fitness, finance, and more.

Company Description

About SEEK

SEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities. We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.

Life at SEEK

SEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do. Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Places to Work in Technology (2021-2024). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.

Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting.

Job Description

Help Shape the Future of Data at SEEK

At SEEK, we’re on a mission to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives. In our Technology and AI teams, data is at the heart of that mission – powering smarter decisions, powering AI innovation, and creating product experiences that truly matter.

As a Solution Architect in our Data & AI domain, you’ll be a trusted thought leader and hands‑on partner, helping to set the direction for SEEK’s data platforms and ensuring our solutions deliver measurable business and customer value. This is your opportunity to work alongside some of the best in the industry, within a collaborative, high‑trust environment that values curiosity, innovation, and continuous learning.

About the role

You will sit at the intersection of technology strategy and delivery execution – working across SEEK’s Technology and AI teams to translate big aspirations into actionable architecture roadmaps and pragmatic solutions. Your role blends deep technical expertise with influence, governance, and leadership in the data architecture space.

What you’ll be doing

Shape the vision – Define and evolve SEEK’s architecture strategy and roadmaps for data, analytics, and AI solutions.
Lead with impact – Champion architectural best practice to ensure all data solutions are robust, scalable, and aligned with SEEK standards.
Enable autonomy – Establish guardrails and principles that empower teams to make aligned technology decisions.
Work with delivery teams – Collaborate closely with engineers and data specialists to influence design and operational best practice.
Explore what’s next – Research and assess new technologies, recommending adoption where they deliver value.
Protect the business – Identify architectural risks early and recommend effective mitigation strategies.
Connect and influence – Communicate complex architectural decisions clearly to both technical and non‑technical audiences.

About the team

You’ll join SEEK’s high‑performing Architecture function of 25+ professionals spanning six key domains: Enterprise, Customer, Data & AI, Platform, Growth, and Architecture Practices. Your focus will be within Data & AI Architecture, supporting Data Services, AI Analytics, and SEEK’s broader AI‑powered ambitions. We’re collaborative, outcome‑focused, and love solving big, complex problems that make a difference for millions of users.

Qualifications

Technical expertise

Extensive experience in data architecture – including modelling, warehousing, lakes, ETL/ELT, and modern data platforms.
Strong knowledge of batch/real‑time processing, event‑driven designs, and building scalable pipelines across mixed database environments.
Experience with analytics platforms, visualisation tools, and integrating ML capabilities for advanced analytics.
Proven expertise in data governance – frameworks, catalogues, lineage, metadata, privacy‑by‑design, classification, and access control.
Background in enterprise integration and data management – including interoperability, federation, MDM, and data quality improvement.

Personal skills

Strategic vision – Balance big‑picture thinking with practical delivery.
Collaborative mindset – Work well across tech and business domains.
Problem‑solving – Break down complexity into actionable steps.
Continuous learner – Adapt quickly and stay ahead in a changing tech landscape.
Influential communicator – Engage, motivate, and influence stakeholders at all levels.
Outcome‑driven – Consistently focus on delivering business value.
Additional Information

Permanent Perks
At SEEK we offer:

Annual Performance Bonus Plan
Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.
Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave

At SEEK, we are passionate about fostering a culture of inclusion and wellbeing that embraces and values the diversity of our people. We are a purpose driven business that works with heart.

We know teams with diverse ideas, experiences and perspectives are more creative and are critical to ensuring effective delivery and innovating to enable our future success. As such, we welcome applications from people with diverse backgrounds and life experiences, especially as they relate to gender, sexual identity, culture, faith, disability and life stages. Should you require any specific support or adjustments throughout the recruitment process and beyond, please advise us and we will be happy to assist.

For this role, only those candidates with the eligible right to work will be considered.

SEEK kindly requests no unsolicited resumes or approaches from recruitment agencies and will not be responsible for any associated fees.

Job Title: Head of Data Governance, Privacy and Regulatory Analytics
Ad Text:
Unique, highly visible role, working with a well-regarded executive leadership team.
Excellent work life balance and a real opportunity to have immediate impact
Sydney Based. Up to $250k base + super + Benefits
About the Role:

We are seeking a Head of Data Governance, Privacy, and Regulatory Analytics to lead and shape the organisation’s approach to regulatory data strategy, privacy frameworks, and governance. This is a pivotal leadership role in a highly data-driven environment, working closely with regulators and senior stakeholders to ensure compliance while driving innovation and efficiency.

Key Responsibilities:

Regulatory Data Strategy: Develop and implement strategies to meet regulatory requirements, including Economic and Financial Statistics (EFS) reporting and Open Banking compliance.
Regulator Engagement: Build and maintain strong relationships with regulatory bodies such as APRA, ASIC ACCC and OAIC, ensuring accurate and transparent communication.
Data Governance Leadership: Establish and maintain frameworks for data ownership, lineage, and retention, ensuring the integrity and quality of critical data elements (CDEs).
Privacy Oversight: Manage first-line privacy responsibilities, including Privacy Impact Assessments and embedding privacy by design into business processes.
Cross-Team Collaboration: Partner with risk, compliance, and technology teams to deliver integrated data solutions aligned with regulatory and business objectives.
Continuous Improvement: Stay ahead of evolving regulatory requirements, driving innovation and efficiency in data systems and reporting processes.
What We’re Looking For:

We’re seeking a dynamic leader with a strong regulatory focus, technical expertise, and the ability to bridge the gap between data systems and compliance.

Proven leadership in data governance within financial services, including managing CDEs, data lineage, and retention.
Extensive experience in regulatory reporting, particularly EFS and Open Banking standards.
Strong technical understanding of data systems and architecture.
Demonstrated success in engaging with regulators and representing organisational positions.
Hands-on experience with privacy frameworks, including Privacy Impact Assessments.
Exceptional communication skills to translate complex regulatory requirements for diverse audiences.
Strategic thinker with the ability to anticipate regulatory changes and their implications.
Relevant industry qualifications/professional certifications in risk management or compliance.
Ready to Apply?

If you’re a data-driven professional with a passion for regulatory compliance, privacy, and governance, we’d love to hear from you. This is your chance to make a significant impact in a challenging and rewarding leadership role.
This role offers a unique blend of technical, regulatory, and leadership challenges. If you’re ready to take on this exciting opportunity, apply now!
For a confidential chat, contact Jen Jones at Ink Recruitment on +61 (0)409 926 897.

Our client, a retail company, is looking for a Commercial Analyst to join their team on a 9-month basis. There is a possibility of extension or permanency with this role for the right candidate. The office is based in Surry Hills and hybrid working is available.

Daily rate - $500-530 per day + super, dependent on experience


Responsibilities

Analyse promotional activities to optimise return on investment and assess new investment opportunities.
Identify opportunities for gross margin improvement and cost reduction, including product lifecycle and rationalisation analysis.
Prepare financial models and strategic analysis to support long-term planning and decision-making.
Deliver accurate business performance reports and commentary, including month-end tasks and reconciliations.
Lead Onestream implementation and manage monthly data uploads.
Provide data-driven insights to support strategic decisions across sales, marketing, and product development.
Develop pricing models and analyse product range rationalisation aligned with business strategy.
Participate in budgeting, rolling forecasts, and strategic financial planning activities.

Job Title: Senior Investment Analytics and Insights Analyst
Ad Text:
About Cbus
 
Created by workers, for workers, Cbus Super is one of Australia’s most successful Superannuation funds. For almost four decades we’ve proudly represented those who help shape Australia, hard-working individuals who deserve to make the most of their retirement, no matter the industry. As an award-winning fund we’ve been recognised for the benefits provided to our members and our innovative investment approach.  All while staying committed to our member first ethos as a proud Industry Fund.
 
About the role
 
The Senior Investment Analytics and Insights Analyst is pivotal in driving the fund’s digital transformation and enhancing investment decision making. Reporting to the Manager, Investment Insights & Reporting you will support the investment team by delivering data-driven insights and sophisticated analytics through business intelligence tools, enabling a whole-of-fund perspective on performance and risk.
 
The ideal candidate will bring expertise in integrating diverse data sources, building insightful dashboards and working within multi-asset environments. Your deep understanding of investment data and systems will ensure that key metrics are monitored effectively, making this role essential to optimising investment outcomes and strategic fund management.
 
Key Accountabilities

Design and deliver data-driven analytics solutions by collaborating with stakeholders to understand reporting needs
Develop and maintain PowerBI dashboards and data workflows using SQL and data modelling to optimize reporting and insights
Enhance and automate existing reporting processes replacing manual Excel models with scalable data-driven solutions
Support data governance initiatives, including documentation, glossaries and integration with governance tools
Provide training and collaborate across teams to improve data literacy, share knowledge and support long term analytics capabilities
What will you bring?

Experience in a similar Data Analyst or Analytics and Insights Analyst role specifically working with multi asset Investment Data
Strong expertise in SQL, data modeling and building reusable data assets using tools like Excel or Python
Effective communicator and collaborator with experience working across complex stakeholder environments
Proactive and accountable with a focus on automating processes and improving data quality and governance
Knowledge of third-party investment systems such as Factset, Ortec, Pearl, BarraOne, RIMES, Datastream and/or Bloomberg preferred
Exposure to using Microsoft Azure, including managing cloud-based data solutions and supporting platform integration
Belong at Cbus
 
We value difference, and embrace people with diverse backgrounds, experiences, gender identities, abilities and thinking styles. We believe that, with diversity of perspectives and experiences, you get better teams and outcomes. We’re looking for people of all genders, races, nationalities, orientations and of all abilities to join us.
 
We’re keen to hear from you
 
If you've read through the requirements of this role and you feel like you haven’t fully met the criteria, we would still encourage you to apply. We're aware of accessibility barriers when it comes to applying for a job and we want to help. If you require assistance with your application, please contact our Talent Acquisition Team via careers@cbussuper.com.au 
 
Like to know more about working with Cbus? Listen to some of our videos with members of the Cbus team on our website, cbussuper.com.au/careers
 
Applications Close: Tuesday 14 October 2025 
 
This is a full-time position based in Melbourne
 
Agencies, please note: All Cbus vacancies are managed by our internal Talent Acquisition Team.  Should external assistance be required we will reach out to our preferred agency partners, Thank you.

About us

From humble roots in Eromanga, QLD, we’ve been fuelling the furthest corners of Australia for over 40 years. But we think the most exciting journey’s still on the horizon.

Joining IOR puts you in the driver’s seat. You'll get the opportunity to own your ambition and build a worthwhile career - all while seeing your impact on the faces of your team and the communities we serve. You won't see our logo on racing cars, but you will be part of a team that helps fuel LifeFlight's choppers.

Whether you’re driving trucks, designing tech, manufacturing tanks or managing logistics behind the scenes, a career with IOR means going further, in every sense of the word - in your relationships, your impact and your remarkable career.

Right team

Work with people you trust and form relationships that will go the distance
Build something great with a team that will have a laugh and have your back

Right Track

So many career opportunities to explore... and you’re in the driver’s seat
Grow with us at IOR - the bigger we get, the bigger your opportunities become

Right Now

We want you to succeed, so you’re given trust and autonomy to do what it takes
Real momentum, real impact and the sense that there’s plenty more to come

About your role,

We are looking for a highly skilled and motivated Senior Data Scientist to join our growing team at IOR. This role plays a critical part in building a world-class data capability to enhance commercial decision-making, drive margin expansion, and improve operational efficiency. You will work closely with leadership and business teams to design advanced analytics models, unlock insights, and develop tools that power everyday business decisions.

Accelerate enterprise value by embedding performance analytics, pricing intelligence, and data-driven strategy to drive growth and optimise margins.
Embed advanced analytics at scale through machine learning, automation, and scenario modelling to inform operations, strategy, and commercial outcomes.
Elevate pricing performance with custom pricing frameworks driven by market data, operational systems, and IOR’s proprietary Dashboard platform.
Deliver strategic insights by translating complex data into simple, actionable recommendations that influence leadership decisions and operational execution.
Uplift analytical maturity by developing scalable tools, mentoring analysts, and collaborating with tech teams to enhance IOR’s data architecture and capability.

About you

To succeed in this role, you will need the following attributes:

Educational foundation in Data Science, Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering, or a related discipline (Bachelor’s or Master’s required).
Proven technical expertise in supervised machine learning, statistical modelling, simulations, and advanced programming (Python, R, SQL).
Strong analytical capabilities with experience in large-scale data visualisation, real-time analytics, and cloud infrastructure (preferably Azure).
Experience in advanced analytics, with added value for backgrounds in Monte Carlo simulation, predictive pricing, and supply chain optimisation.
Commercially focused mindset, blending Agile practices with the ability to link analytical outputs to business performance and mentor others.

Why join IOR?

You can feel it from day one. The energy, the growth… the sense that this place is going somewhere. And you're not just along for the ride. You’re behind the wheel.

IOR’s the kind of place where you put your name to a project, and you own it. The wins, the challenges, and everything in between we back you to see it through, even when things don’t go to plan. Support is always there if you need it. Otherwise, you’re trusted to do what it takes to keep things running.

You don’t get that in too many places.

Approaching each day through our values of Innovation finding solutions, Our Communities serving people, and Reliability getting results, our team is focused on delivering what really matters to our customers. It’s this mindset that drives us forward.

The best part? As we grow bigger, the opportunities get bigger, too. Backed by a solid strategy and a right to win, joining our team means more projects, more challenges, and more chances to stretch yourself.

What does this mean for you?

Be part of an unbeatable culture where people really do enjoy coming to work
Investment in your career through training and development programs, ongoing support, plus the backing to take your career in whichever direction you choose
Work hard, play hard with our Blue Squad - trivias, barbecues and plenty of laughs!
Staff and family discounts on fuel (obviously!)

Ready to go further with IOR?

If this sounds like you, don't overthink it - just apply! We're looking forward to meeting you.

We provide an equal employment opportunity for all; we see the value in diversity and celebrate individuality. This looks like respectful conversations and a safe workplace where everyone thrives.

How will your ideas contribute to shaping what's next?

Could You Be Our Senior Supply Chain Solutions Lead?

Excellent communication, negotiation, and stakeholder management capabilities.
Proven ability to lead through ambiguity and deliver results in fast-paced, dynamic settings.
Bachelor's degree in Supply Chain, Business, Engineering, or a related field is beneficial.
